						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1467, Krōdhi, Śrāvaṇa, ba. 7, Śanivāra</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1544 August 9, Saturday,</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Sadāśiva-Mahārāya.</hi> It records that, under the orders of the king, <hi rend="bold">Rāmarājaya</hi> granted an order to his barber <hi rend="bold">Koṇḍōja,</hi> exempting the barbers from the tax <hi rend="italic">siddhāya.</hi></p>						

